# UI Design System

Use this rule for presentation and styling. Combine with `project-protection.mdc`: visuals may change; behavior must not.

## Stack & sources of truth

- Vite + React 18 (JSX), Tailwind, shadcn under `src/components/ui/**`
- Tokens: `src/index.css` (`--go-*`) + Tailwind `go-*` / `bg-go-*` / `text-go-*`
- Prefer tokens over one-off hex / `border-white/` / `text-[10px]`
- Icons: `lucide-react`
- Imports: `@/…`

## Token quick reference

| Role | CSS | Tailwind examples |
|------|-----|-------------------|
| App background | `--go-bg` | `bg-go-bg` / `bg-background` |
| Surface | `--go-surface` | `bg-go-surface` / `bg-card` |
| Muted surface | `--go-surface-muted` | `bg-go-surface-muted` |
| Text | `--go-text` / secondary / muted | `text-go-text`, `text-go-text-muted` |
| Border | `--go-border` / strong | `border-go-border` |
| Brand | `--go-primary` / hover | `bg-go-primary`, `hover:bg-go-primary-hover` |
| Status | success / warning / danger / info | `text-go-success`, `bg-go-danger-muted` |
| Type | page / section / body / label / meta | `text-go-page`, `text-go-body`, `text-go-meta` |
| Radius | `--go-radius*` | `rounded-go`, `rounded-go-sm`, `rounded-go-lg` |
| Shadow | `--go-shadow-*` | `shadow-go-sm` |
| Control height | `--go-control-h` | `h-go-control` (40px) |

Light theme is default. Dark uses `.dark` class with non–pure-black surfaces.

## Shared components (`src/components/shared`)

Prefer these for new presentation work:

- `PageHeader`, `SectionHeader`, `DataPanel`, `DefinitionList`
- `StatusBadge` (icon + text; replace MinimalBadge for new UI)
- `EmptyState`, `LoadingState`, `ErrorState`
- `SearchInput`, `IconButton`, `CopyButton`

Import from `@/components/shared` or specific files. Keep them presentational only.

## Presentational rules

- Prefer existing shadcn primitives; do not fork `src/components/ui/**` unless necessary
- New UI helpers stay presentational: no new API/entity/auth calls inside them
- Restyle loading / error / empty / success UI without changing when they appear or what data they use
- Responsive and a11y improvements are encouraged (focus, labels, contrast, keyboard) without changing flows
- Microcopy may be clarified; meaning and outcomes must stay the same
- Avoid AI-generic chrome: glassmorphism, neon, pulse décor, gradient text, purple accent spam

## Layout & hierarchy

- Match nearby pages/components; one sibling pattern over inventing new folders/libs
- Improve spacing, type scale, and hierarchy with Tailwind + `var(--go-*)`
- Animations: subtle presence/hierarchy only — do not gate or replace business actions
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Out of scope for UI work

- `base44/entities/**`, entity wrappers, `localClient` / Base44 client query shapes
- Auth context, route guards, permissions, env wiring
- Validation schemas, calculations, data transforms, mock data swaps

## Change discipline

- Small diffs: style and structure first; preserve handlers and query keys
- Before edit: list preserved logic in the file (even briefly)
- After edit: run build; fix only UI-caused failures
